[SN]TITLE[SN]
Taking the Paralympic Challenge

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Have you ever wondered what it is like to be a visually impaired athlete?

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
10 March 2016 Last updated at 12:39 GMT
School Reporters from Copthall School in Barnet visited Lee Valley Athletics Centre to take part in the Active Kids Paralympic Challenge in a bid to answer that question.
With the help of Paralympian Libby Clegg and Britain's top female sprinter, Dina Asher-Smith, they learned what it is like to run with limited vision and how an athlete's sighted guide also plays an important role.
